    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offensive engine is anchored today by **Luis Robert Jr.**, who earns our highest daily efficiency score of 75.16. His matchup against Eduardo Rodriguez provides a significant +14% boost due to the platoon advantage, and despite a slightly unfavorable park factor, his presence in the three-hole makes him our premier start. **Jacob Wilson** (64.54) also projects well out of the leadoff spot against Ryan Weathers; the +10% boost for hitting at the top of the order coupled with a favorable park adjustment makes him an essential component of our pursuit of runs and batting average today. While **Jackson Merrill** (60.44) and **Miguel Vargas** (60.08) hover just above our threshold for strong starts, both benefit from favorable order placement and park factors that nudge their raw projections into the \"Strong\" category, ensuring we capitalize on potential RBI opportunities.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Liam Hicks**, who finished with a score of 39.83. Ultimately, the projection model relegated him to the bench as he fell just shy of our \"Zebras Floor\" of 40.0. The primary drag on his score was an unfavorable matchup against Andrew Lowder, whose 3.31 xERA represents an elite arm that suppresses his efficiency despite the platoon advantage. Elsewhere, the absence of stalwarts like **Kyle Tucker**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** due to scheduled off-days forces us to rely heavily on the remaining active roster. With **Andy Pages**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Josh Lowe**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Nolan Schanuel** monitoring the situation from the bench, we must remain disciplined with our game caps. Watch the weather reports closely, as any shift in wind patterns could diminish the modest +5% boost currently favoring **Miguel Vargas**.",
